Package utility

Interface List

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SLL

    public interface List
    The List interface described below is the basis for learning Linear data types. It is not as involved as the java.util.List. It will not define any iteration methods that would normally be a part of the List interface.

        Method to append an element to the end of a List. If the list is empty the element will be added to the first position.

      • add

        boolean add​(java.lang.Object element)
        Method to add an element to the FIRST position in the list. If the list is empty, the element will be added to the first position.
        Parameters:
        element - - element to be added to the list

      • add

        boolean add​(java.lang.Object element,
            int position)
     throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Method to add an element to a specific position in the list. If the position is an index outside of the bounds of the list an exception is raised.
        Parameters:
        element - - element to be added to the list
        position - - index that the element should be placed at
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the index is (position<0 || position > size())

        Clears the list, all elements are lost

      • remove

        java.lang.Object remove​()
        Removes the FIRST element in the list and changes the index for all the remaining elements by (-1).
        Returns:
        Object element at the first position of the list. If the list is empty, returns a null reference.

      • removeLast

        java.lang.Object removeLast​()
        Removes the LAST element in the list.
        Returns:
        Object element at the last position of the list. If list is empty, returns a null reference.

      • remove

        java.lang.Object remove​(int position)
                 throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Removes the element at the provided index, if the index is outside the bounds of the the list an exception is thrown
        Parameters:
        position - the position in the list of the element to be removed
        Returns:
        Object element being removed from the list
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the index is (position<0 || position >= size())

      • get

        java.lang.Object get​()
        Gets a reference to the first element in the list without disturbing the list structure.
        Returns:
        Object reference to the first element in the list, if the list is empty, returns a null reference.

      • getLast

        java.lang.Object getLast​()
        Gets a reference to the last element in the list, without disturbing the list structure.
        Returns:
        Object reference to the last element in the list, if the list is empty, returns a null reference.

      • get

        java.lang.Object get​(int position)
              throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Gets a reference to the element at the specified position. If the List is empty returns a null reference.
        Parameters:
        position - the location within the list of the desired element
        Returns:
        Object reference to the specified element
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the index is (position< 0 || position >= size())

                     int position)
              throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Replaces the element at the specified position in this list with the specified element.
        Parameters:

        position - - index of the element to replace
        Returns:
        Object reference to the element previously stored at the specified position
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the index is (position< 0 || position >= size())

      • contains

        boolean contains​(java.lang.Object element)
        Checks the list and determines if the object exists in the list, if the object is present in the list, the method returns true.
        Parameters:
        element - - element being located in list
        Returns:
        boolean true if object is in list, otherwise false.

      • indexOf

        int indexOf​(java.lang.Object element)
        Returns the index in this list of the first occurrence of the specified element, or -1 if the List does not contain this element.
        Parameters:
        element - - element being located in list
        Returns:
        int, the index in this list of the first occurrence of the specified element, or -1 if the list does not contain this element.

      • size

        int size​()
        Gets the current number of elements in the list, if list is empty returns a 0 (zero).
        Returns:
        int, an integer greater or equal to zero

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty​()
        Returns the current status of the list.
        Returns:
        boolean false if the list contains any elements.
